@* ============================================
   MOBILE/TABLET GRADIENT CENTERING STRATEGY
   ============================================
   
   Desktop (≥992px):
   - Wide, immersive gradients positioned at screen edges
   - Gradients create atmospheric backdrop across entire viewport
   - No backdrop-filter on hero content for clean presentation
   
   Tablet (≤991px):
   - Gradients repositioned to center behind hero content
   - Creates focused, premium frame around headline, CTAs, badges
   - Subtle backdrop-filter enhances text legibility
   
   Mobile Portrait (≤767px):
   - Tighter gradient focus directly behind core content
   - Enhanced backdrop-filter (blur + dark overlay) for AA accessibility
   - Text shadows ensure minimum 4.5:1 contrast ratio
   
   Small Phones (≤575px):
   - Maximum content focus with minimal gradient distraction
   - Stronger backdrop ensures content remains readable
   - Gradients frame content without crowding edges
   
   Implementation Notes:
   - All gradient positioning uses transform: translateX(-50%) for perfect centering
   - Gradients scale down progressively on smaller screens
   - Blur increases on mobile to soften background without losing depth
   - Opacity carefully balanced: visible ambiance without overwhelming text
   - Safe area insets respected for notched devices (iPhone, Android)
   
   Accessibility:
   - Text contrast maintained at WCAG AA level (4.5:1 minimum)
   - Text shadows provide additional contrast layer
   - Backdrop-filter creates clear separation from animated background
   - Reduced motion respected via prefers-reduced-motion query
*@

